<!------------------------------------------------------------------------ingredients----------->
<p3>Japanese Mayonnaise</p3>
<ul1><font size="4">
<li>3 tbsp mayonnaise</li>
<li>1 tbsp rice wine vinegar</li>
<li>1 tsp soy sauce</li>
</ul1></font>
<p>Sushi</p>
<ul2>
<li>300g sushi rice</li>
<li>100ml rice wine vinegar</li>
<li>2 tbsp golden caster sugar</li>
<li>25g nori sheets</li>
<li>Filling (your choice)</li>

</ul2>
<!-----------------------------------------------------------------instructions--------------------------------->
<ol>
<font size="4">
<li>Pat out rice and lay a nori sheet on the sushi mat with the shiny side down. Pat handfuls of rice with vinegared water. Pat rice on top 1 cm thick with the edge furthest away from you clear.</li>
<li>Spread Japanese Mayo down the rice</li>
<li>Add the filling of ypur choice</li>
<li>Roll the mat, apply light preasure when rolling.</li>
<li>Wrap the sushi in plastic wrap and cut into pieces</li>







</ol>
</font>

